-- Former SAC Capital Advisors President Tom Conheeney leaves firm
-- By Svea Herbst-Bayliss
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 09:42AM EDT
-- None



BOSTON, Aug 18 (Reuters) - Thomas Conheeney, who was president of Steven A. Cohen's SAC Capital Advisors during the years the hedge fund was being investigated for insider trading, has stepped down and left  successor organization Point72 Asset Management, it said on Monday.

Douglas Haynes will succeed Conheeney at Point72 Asset Management, the successor to SAC after the hedge fund pleaded guilty to insider trading charges and transformed into a so-called family office.